.\" ###### Setup ############################################################
.Dd May 11, 2026
.Dt encrypt\-dbeaver\-configuration 1
.Os encrypt\-dbeaver\-configuration
.\" ###### Name #############################################################
.Sh NAME
.Nm encrypt\-dbeaver\-configuration
.Nd Encrypt DBeaver Credentials Configuration File
.\" ###### Synopsis #########################################################
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm encrypt\-dbeaver\-configuration Ar plain\_dbeaver\_credentials\_config\_json Ar encrypted\_dbeaver\_credentials\_config\_json
.Nm encrypt\-dbeaver\-configuration
.Op Fl h | Fl Fl help
.Nm encrypt\-dbeaver\-configuration
.Op Fl v | Fl Fl version
.\" ###### Description ######################################################
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm encrypt\-dbeaver\-configuration
encrypts a plain\-text DBeaver credentials configuration file.
"\-" can be used as placeholder for
.Pa /dev/stdin ,
to read the input file from standard input.
"\-" can be used as placeholder for
.Pa /dev/stdout ,
to write the output file to standard output.
.Pp
.\" ###### Arguments ########################################################
.Sh ARGUMENTS
The following arguments may be provided:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ar plain\_dbeaver\_credentials\_config\_json
The input plain\-text DBeaver credentials configuration JSON file, or "\-" for
.Pa /dev/stdin .
.It Ar encrypted\_dbeaver\_credentials\_config\_json
The output encrypted DBeaver credentials configuration JSON file, or "\-" for
.Pa /dev/stdout .
.It Fl h | Fl Fl help
Prints command help.
.It Fl v | Fl Fl version
Prints program version.
.El
.\" ###### Exit status ######################################################
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The
.Nm
tool exits with 0 on success, and >0 in case of an error.
.\" ###### Examples #########################################################
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It encrypt\-dbeaver\-configuration plaintext.json $DBEAVER\_DIR/credentials\-config.json
.It encrypt\-dbeaver\-configuration \-\-version
.It encrypt\-dbeaver\-configuration \-h
.El
